comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-20T09:55:48.345Z",claude-code-agent,"Root-cause + fix iteration (verified against the real per-PR windows-latest job, not just nightly):\n\n1. The differentiator is NOT absolute-vs-relative specifier — it is whether Vite TRANSFORMS the module. A fully dynamic `import()` (specifier begins with `${...}`) is opaque to Vite, so on Windows the `.mjs` is loaded untransformed and its `#!/usr/bin/env node` shebang reaches the module compiler → `SyntaxError: Invalid or unexpected token` (empty stack). On Linux the runtime resolver happens to transform it, which is why it was green there.\n\n2. First attempt (relative `file://`-free specifier computed from the helper dir) STILL failed the windows-regression job — still fully dynamic, still untransformed.\n\n3. Working fix: Vite's `dynamic-import-vars` plugin only rewrites an `import()` when the static parts include a directory prefix AND a file extension, and the variable may span only ONE path segment. So `../../scripts/${name}.mjs` works; `../../${path}` (no static ext) is rejected ('file extension must be in the static part'), and `../../scripts/${'release/utils'}.mjs` is rejected ('variables only represent file names one level deep') — hence the explicit `scripts/release/${name}.mjs` branch for the single nested dir.\n\n4. The per-call cache-bust query had to be dropped (it broke the glob-map lookup: 'Unknown variable dynamic import: …?v=n1'); `vi.resetModules()` in the harness afterEach already provides per-test freshness and keeps relative `vi.doMock` targets matching.\n\n5. Hardened the per-PR `windows-regression` CI job to run all of `tests/unit/scripts/` so this class is caught per-PR (it is what surfaced both the original miss and my first failed attempt within minutes instead of waiting for nightly)."
files[3]{path,scope,note}:
  tests/helpers/scriptModule.ts,project,Route .mjs script imports through Windows-safe relative specifiers
  .github/workflows/ci.yml,project,Broaden per-PR windows-regression job to cover tests/unit/scripts/
  tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts,project,Lock broadened windows-regression command
body: "## Summary\n\npm-i84i was closed 2026-06-20T01:37 after replacing `file://`-URL TypeScript source imports (`tests/helpers/sourceModule.ts`) with Vitest-transformable relative specifiers and adding a per-PR `windows-regression` job. But the next nightly (run 27864828585, 2026-06-20T07:52, commit 88aa1cbf — which already contained that fix) was **still red**.\n\nRoot cause: the **other** test helper, `tests/helpers/scriptModule.ts` (`createScriptHarness`), was not touched. Its `importModule`/`importModuleStable` import repo `.mjs` scripts via an absolute `pathToFileURL(...).href` (+ cache-bust query). On Windows, Vitest does **not** intercept that `file:///D:/...` specifier for transformation, so the script's leading `#!/usr/bin/env node` shebang survives into the module compiler and throws `SyntaxError: Invalid or unexpected token` at the `#`. Every test in the 28 `tests/unit/scripts/**` specs (plus the OTEL integration spec that imports a script) fails identically — matching the observed fan-out (dogfood-package-first 31/31, finalize-build 3/3, bundle-cli, run-tests, release/*, etc.).\n\nThe per-PR `windows-regression` job pm-i84i added only ran `cli-main-errors.spec.ts` + `runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts`, so it never exercised the script-harness path — which is why the per-PR check stayed green while the nightly went red again.\n\n## Fix\n\n1. `tests/helpers/scriptModule.ts`: route both `importModule` and `importModuleStable` through a relative specifier computed from the helper's own module URL (`../../<relativePath>`, POSIX separators), mirroring `sourceModule.ts`. Vitest then transforms the module and strips the shebang on every platform.\n2. Broaden the per-PR `windows-regression` CI job to also run the whole `tests/unit/scripts/` directory, so this entire class fails a required per-PR check, not just the nightly. Lock it in `ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `scriptModule.ts` imports scripts via relative specifiers; no absolute `file://` URL.\n- [ ] All `tests/unit/scripts/**` specs pass on Linux (no regression) and on windows-latest in the per-PR job.\n- [ ] Per-PR `windows-regression` job covers `tests/unit/scripts/`.\n- [ ] Coverage stays 100/100/100/100; no new `any`.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Still-red nightly: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/actions/runs/27864828585 (commit 88aa1cbf, post-pm-i84i)\n- GitHub issue: #315"
